int32_t VLIB_unpackMask32 (const uint32_t *restrict mask32packed, uint8_t *restrict maskImage, const uint32_t pixelCount)

Function Documentation

int32_t VLIB_unpackMask32 ( const uint32_t *restrict  mask32packed,
uint8_t *restrict  maskImage,
const uint32_t  pixelCount 
)

Description:
This function unpacks 32-bit packed binary data to a 8-bit unpacked format (each 32 bits of input converts to 32 bytes output).
Parameters:
[in] mask32packed 32-bit packed binary mask buffer (32-bit packed)
[out] maskImage Unpacked binary mask image buffer (UQ8.0)
[in] pixelCount Number of pixels to process (UQ32.0)
Assumptions:
  • I/O buffers are assumed to be double-word aligned and not aliased.
  • The pixelCount must be a multiple of 8.
Implementation Notes:
  • This code is fully interruptible
  • This code is compatible with C64X+ fixed-point processors
Benchmarks:
See VLIB_Test_Report.html for cycle and memory information.
